Package space.sunqian.fs.object.data

Interface ObjectSchemaParser

@ThreadSafe public interface ObjectSchemaParser
This interface is used to parse Type to ObjectSchema. It uses a list of ObjectSchemaParser.Handlers to execute the specific parsing operations, where each ObjectSchemaParser.Handler possesses its own specific parsing logic.

There is a skeletal handler implementation: AbstractObjectSchemaHandler. And the default parser is based on SimpleBeanSchemaHandler.

    • parse

      @Nonnull default @Nonnull ObjectSchema parse(@Nonnull @Nonnull Type type) throws DataObjectException
      Parses the given type to an instance of ObjectSchema, and returns the parsed ObjectSchema.

      The parsing logic of the implementations must be: invokes the ObjectSchemaParser.Handler.parse(ObjectSchemaParser.Context) in the order of handlers() until one of the handlers returns false. The codes are similar to: 

      
 for (Handler handler : handlers()) {
     if (!handler.parse(context)) {
         break;
     }
 }

      Note that this method does not cache the results and will generate new instances every invocation.

      Parameters:
      type - the given type
      Returns:
      the parsed ObjectSchema
      Throws:
      DataObjectException - if any problem occurs
